# Move Trainer 3 — Opponents Move

When adding or editing **`/move-trainer/move-trainer-3/opponents-move-*`** flows:

## Product scope

- **Variant 1 (small coach, two bubbles):** commentary on White’s reply + second bubble with **Play …** / turn strip. Do **not** add **Continue** or other CTAs unless the user explicitly asks (Continue belongs to **variant 2** pacing).
- **Variant 2:** Documented separately when implemented — large scroll bubble, **Video + Continue**, reveal “Play …” only after Continue.

## Footer

- Unless the user specifies otherwise, **OM footer CTAs match Play Move:** **Video + Hint**, plus existing movelist/progress/toolbar shell rules.
- Route change **Play Move → OM → Play Move** may rely on **browser / app back** after Black’s move until product adds an explicit primary CTA.

## Coach layout (`MoveTrainer3LineCoach.vue`)

- OM wrapper **must** use **`move-trainer-3-coach--om-v1`** (or future OM-specific class).
- **Exclude OM** from Intro-only selectors that use `:not(.move-trainer-3-coach--play-move-fill)` — those rules assume Intro movelist layout and force **`min-height`** / margins that break OM “hug content” bubbles.
- `CoachBubble` uses fixed **~116px** row/min-heights for generic and informational branches; OM needs **scoped `:deep()` overrides** so bubbles **hug copy** (do not ship OM with empty vertical padding from DS defaults).

## Isolation

- Do not reuse **`panel-footer-v10--assisted-quiz`** or other footer variants on OM unless requested (see `footer-variants-isolation.mdc`).
